      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType" reg="sculpture"><rs type="decoration">head</rs></rs>, broken off from a lost statue, of a
<rs type="decoration">bearded male</rs>, probably of the first half of the fifth century.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p>The text is <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">cut</rs> on the top of the head, on the smooth area
immediately behind the ridge of curly hair crowning the face, to be
read from the front.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>Carefully cut, but varying in size from <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.01-0.015</measure> in the first line to
<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.0175</measure> to <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.02</measure> (<term>beta</term>) and <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.028</measure> (<term>eta</term>) in the second
line.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date notAfter="0500" exact="none" notBefore="0301">Fourth to fifth centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">content</rs>, <rs type="criteria">location</rs>).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
		<ab><lb n="1"/><w lemma="ΧΜΓ">ΧΜΓ</w> <lb n="2"/><w lemma="θεός"><persName type="divine" key="God" full="yes"><expan><abbr>Θ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ε</supplied><abbr>ὲ</abbr></expan></persName></w> <w lemma="βοηθέω">βοήθι</w>.</ab>
      </div>

     

      <div><head>Apparatus</head>   <p>l. 1, perhaps <foreign lang="grc"><persName key="Christ" type="divine" full="yes"><expan><abbr>Χ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ριστὸν</supplied></expan></persName> <persName key="Mary" type="divine" full="yes"><expan><abbr>Μ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αρία</supplied></expan></persName> <expan><abbr>Γ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">εννᾷ</supplied></expan></foreign></p></div><div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab><seg cert="low">M<supplied reason="abbreviation">ary</supplied> b<supplied reason="abbreviation">ore</supplied> Ch<supplied reason="abbreviation">rist</supplied></seg>. God, help.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="VIII.20">VIII.20</xref>, and compare <xref type="inscription" n="31" href="030008">3.8</xref>.ii.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p> <rs type="found">No details; in <rs type="monuList">collection</rs>.</rs> <rs type="origLocation">Unknown.</rs> <rs type="lastLocation">Musée du Cinquentenaire, Brussels (1988)</rs></p></div>

      

      

      <div type="history" n="record">
        <head>History of Recording</head>
        <p>Excavated by <rs type="visitor" key="gaudin">Gaudin</rs>: on the provenance see <bibl><author>K. T. Erim</author>,
'De Aphrodisiade', <title level="m">AM</title> 71 (<date value="1967" notBefore="1967" notAfter="1967" exact="both">1967</date>), 236</bibl>.</p>
      </div>

